            "text": "and produce viral proteins . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "For this reason , several intracellular factors ,",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "including the redox state ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "might directly or indirectly affect the progression and outcome of viral infection . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "In physiological conditions , the redox balance between oxidant and antioxidant species is maintained by enzymatic and non - enzymatic systems ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "and it finely regulates several cell functions . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Different viruses break this equilibrium",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "and induce an oxidative stress",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "that in turn facilitates specific steps of the virus lifecycle",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "and activates an inflammatory response . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "In this context , many studies highlighted the importance of redox - sensitive pathways as novel cell - based targets for therapies",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "aimed at blocking both viral replication and virus - induced inflammation . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In the review , we discuss the most recent findings in this field . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "In particular , we describe the effects of natural or synthetic redox - modulating molecules",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "in inhibiting DNA or RNA virus replication as well as inflammatory pathways . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "The importance of the antioxidant transcription factor Nrf2 is also discussed . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
